# 📝 Exercises & Examples


Try these practical exercises to apply what you’ve learned:


🔹 1. Initialize a Git Repository

mkdir my-first-repo
cd my-first-repo
git init


🔹 2. Stage and Commit Changes

echo "# Hello GitHub" > README.md
git add README.md
git commit -m "Add README"


🔹 3. Create and Switch Branches

git branch feature-about
git checkout feature-about
echo "This is the about page." > about.txt
git add about.txt
git commit -m "Add about page"


🔹 4. Merge Changes into Main

git checkout main
git merge feature-about


🔹 5. Push to GitHub

git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/intro-to-github.git
git push -u origin main


🔹 6. Open a Pull Request

On GitHub:

-Create a new branch.

-Push your changes.

-Click "Compare & pull request" to review and submit.

